title: Indian Fairy Tales
creator: Joseph Jacobs
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Indian Fairy Tales, by Joseph Jacobs. This book is a fine collection of Indian fairy tales, some are folklore, some are from the Jataka tales, and some from panchatantra. (Summary by sidhu177) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (181MB)
